@node "What Is" "What is GuideFiler?"
GuideFiler is a professional filelister for CNet3.05+.

Features:

    - Includes FileIDs from nearly all FileID-processors I know.
      No limitation of 8 lines anymore.
      (f.ex. MaxDiz, q-diz etc.)

    - GuideFiler works with a simple GUI for setting up and making
      the filelists.

    - It strips all MCI- and ANSI-Codes.

    - Saves filelist as an AmigaGuide-file. Thats the most confortable
      way for the users to read filelists.

    - different sorter modes: alphabetical, Chronological etc.

    - Displays FileFlags like the normal Browse or Scan command under
      CNet.(Sysop favorite, Free download, Not validated)

    - Uses Areas to make special filelist for every subject.
@endnode

@node "Install" "Installation"
 ---------------------------
 To run GuideFiler you need:
 ---------------------------

    - bgui.library V37+
    - CNet3+


 ---------------------------
 Installing:
 ---------------------------

    1.  Simply copy the bgui.library to your LIBS: assign.

    2.  Copy the GuideFiler/ directory to your desired location. Make sure
        that GuideFiler.data in in the same directory as GuideFiler.

    3.  Start GuideFiler on the Workbench by doubleclicking on its icon.

    4.  Look at @{"Basic Configuration" link "Basic Configuration" 0} for configuring GuideFiler and setting up
        you subboards and follow these instructions.
@endnode

@node "Basic Configuration" "Basics Configuration"
If you are using GuideFiler for the first time note that you should first
setup GuideFiler areas and subboards. GuideFiler will not take automatically
the datas from CNet like other filelisters do. Ok, its a bit of work, but you
have the possibilty to use areas and your own subboardnames appearing in the
AmigaGuide-output.

There are two possibilities to setup these areas and subboards. Using the
builtin GUI-Setup in GuideFiler or simply by editing GuideFiler.cfg:

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Using the GUI
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

    Adding a single entry:

    1.  StartGuideFiler and click on the button "Setup"

    2.  Now you see two list, the first one is for the areas the other
        is for the subboards.

    3.  Click on the Add-button on the Areas side. Now you can enter
        you desired Areaname and a unique AreaIDNumber. Normally this
        number is automatically choosen but you can set it up manually
        f.ex. for use from cli.

    4.  Click the made Area on the List, and press the add button on
        the subboard side. Enter your desired subboardname and click
        on the popfile button to choose the physical path to the
        subboard (A data/ directory should be present there!).

    5.  Click on the "Save" button and restart GuideFiler. Try your
        made Area.


----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Editing GuideFiler.cfg
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Here is an examples how the config could look like:


    Filelist of HangKOK-BBS    Line 1: a brief description of your BBS_|

    2                          Line 2: Numer of Areas                  |
    PC-Software                Line 3: Description of Area             |
    10                         Line 4: Number of Area                  |
    AMIGA-Software             .                                       |
    0                          .                                      _|

    UDBase1:PC/MISC/           Line 5: The path were the data/         |
                                       directory lies                  |
    PC-Anwender                Line 6: Subboard description as it is   |
                                       shown in the AmigaGuide file    |
    10                         Line 7: Areanumber for this subboard    |
                                                                       |
    UDBase0:AMIGA/MISC/        Line 8: Like Line 5                     |
    PD-Anwender                Line 9: Like Line 6 etc.                |
    0                          Line 10:Area 0...                       |
    .                          .                                       .
    .                          .                                       .
    .                          .                                       .

The Lines 5 and 8 etc. are the Paths where CNet creates his data/ directory
and the files are present. Don't forget to append a "/" if there is no ":" on
the end of the Path! If you use a CD-Rom take the Path from the harddisk. CNet
creates in this case a path on your Harddisk where he puts the data/
directory.

Line 7 and 10 etc. are the Areanumbers. You can f.ex. put all your
graphic-subboards under Areanumber 10. Then you can create a filelist with
only the these subboards in.
@endnode

@node "Files" "The Files"
These files should be present in the directory GuideFiler/

    GuideFiler              The main program

    GuideFiler.cfg          An example configfile

    GuideFiler.data         A data file for GuideFiler

    GuideFiler.guide        This guide
@endnode

@node "Assigns" "The Assigns"


    GuideFiler should have all Assigns CNet: needs, because all
    FileID-processors work diffently. The easiest way is to start & quit CNet
    and then use GuideFiler.
@endnode

@node "Shell" "From Shell"
>       !! To use GuideFiler CNet should not be running at the same time.  !!
>       !! There could be problems if an user accesses the same files as   !!
>       !! GuideFiler does!                                                !!

    GuideFiler can be run with these arguments:


    "GuideFiler GUIDE/A CONFIG/N DAYS/N ALL/S QUIET/S REVERSE/S
                DATE/S SIZE/S NAME/S DOWN/S"

    or simply

    "GuideFiler GUI" to use the GUI (See 2.1)


    GUIDE/A:        Name of output guide.
    AREA/N:         Areanumber to use for the Guide
    DAYS/N:         Include last X days. 0=All days
    ALL/S:          Ignore Areanumbers and create a guide for all
                    subboards
    QUIET/S:        supress output of actual file
                    (If you want to spare time, select this Flag)
    REVERSE/S       sort reverse
    DATE/S          sort by date
    SIZE/S          sort by size
    NAME/S          sort by filename
    DOWN/S          sort by downloads

    Example:

    GuideFiler RAM:HangKOK.guide AREA 10 DAYS 14 DATE REVERSE
@endnode

@node "GUI" "Using the GUI"
>       !! To use GuideFiler CNet should not be running at the same time.  !!
>       !! There could be problems if an user accesses the same files as   !!
>       !! GuideFiler does!                                                !!

    To use the GUI start GuideFiler from a shell with the Argument "GUI" or
    simply click the icon on the workbench.

    I think that all functions should be clear here. Note that you can
    multiselect areas, which is not possible from the shell (yet?).
@endnode

@node "History" "History"
    V0.1    initial programming                                6. May 1995
    V0.2    Added DAYS/N function
    V0.3    Changed MAXLEVEL/N to CONFIG/N
            added some stats stuff
    V0.4    code is now smarter
            Bugfix in stripping some colorcodes
            Date is now in DOS-Form
            added @WIDTH 88 to Guide
            better exeption-handling
            a bit faster?
    V0.5    replaced function TrimString() from E because some systems
            do not support this
            Last Days did not work on OS3.0+ machines. DateToStr works
            differently there
    V0.6    lightspeeded, nearly all important operations in assembler
            speeded with AProf, deleting most of the slow StringF
            commands
    V0.7    displays now time needed for proceeding
    V0.8    displays now real size in bytes instead of DownloadBytes
            Added Favorite,Freedownload,Killed display
    V0.81   workin' on some bugs
    V0.9    sometimes, Guidefiler "forgot" some subboards      11.May 1995
            The Flags were totally wrong escpecially the Freedownload
            On OS3.0 the date in the Guide was displayed like "Today"
            Time for proceeding was calced wrong
            Added ALL/S Arg
            Changed "Offline"(Killed) Flag to "Not validated"
    V1.0    Added GUI
    V1.1    removed memory allocation bug. System could totally crash.
            Added some info stuff.
            GuideFiler now strips all MCI- and ANSI-codes.
            Changed CONFIG/N to AREA/N I think that's better
            Added QUIET/S Mode
    V1.2    Added info stuff...
    V1.3    Removed a nasty bug in ReadArgs processing
            Added info stuff...
    V1.4    Changed GUI completly. Now needs BGUI.library to run.
            lighten up source a bit                            19.May 1995
            fixed a bug rendering the byte sizes.
            Added different sorter modes: name, size, downloads
    V1.5    Added Setup function. Fixed some misc bugs.        22.May 1995
            Fixed a bug in the listview handling.
            If a entry is added, the ID number is automatically
            choosen.
@endnode

